        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/aku-stable/{size}/25198_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-04-02T09:53:21.556Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hopefully this feature will be in Signal v7.39 on Android <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/+1.png?v=12\" title=\":+1:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":+1:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<aside class=\"quote\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"68157\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/greyson-signal/48/2005_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/beta-feedback-for-the-upcoming-android-7-39-release/68157\">Beta feedback for the upcoming Android 7.39 release</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/beta-feedback/android-beta-feedback/97\"><span data-category-id=\"97\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #0088CC; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF; --parent-category-badge-color: #0088CC;\" data-parent-category-id=\"25\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --has-parent\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Android Beta Feedback</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    We’re releasing the Signal 7.39 beta soon. If you’re interested in participating, join the beta group <a href=\"https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/articles/360007318471-\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">here</a>. \nShare your feedback on the latest changes: \n\nNotes TBD, but some higlights \n\nYou can now schedule voice messages (need to lock recording first, then long-press send)\nThe UI for saving lots of media to disk all at once is a lot better\n\n\nComplete list of new commits since 7.38.7: \n<a href=\"https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-Android/compare/v7.38.7...main\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">https://github.com/signalapp/Signal-Android/compare/v7.38.7…main</a> \nThank you for being a beta tester!\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
